    “question”: “What is the core framework: Emotions, Self, Vision, Surroundings?”,
    “answer”: “Emotions: Choose from positive states, not fear, rivalry, anger, or greed.\n\nSelf: Act from your calm, secure core rather than egoic impulse.\n\nVision: Let long-term aspirations orient short-term choices.\n\nSurroundings: Match decisions to the real context. No single formula fits all situations.”,
