    “_id”: { “$oid”: “680c4c3b533ecbc3f962c113” },
    “category”: “science”,
    “question”: “How does breathwork influence decisions physiologically?”,
    “answer”: “Slow nasal breathing increases vagal tone, lifts heart-rate variability (HRV), and shifts the body toward parasympathetic dominance. This reduces threat bias, widens attention, and supports deliberation. Exhales slightly longer than inhales amplify the calming effect.”,
